<taxonomicName authorityName="J. J. Schenk &amp; D. W. Thomas, Novon 14 (2): 227" authorityYear="2004" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Ledermanniella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ledermanniella prasina" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="prasina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Ledermanniella prasina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was assessed as Vulnerable (
<bibRefCitation author="Cheek, M" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B14" refString="Cheek, M, 2017b. Ledermanniellaprasina. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2017: e.T110079107A110079109. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" title="Ledermanniellaprasina. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2017: e. T 110079107 A 110079109. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" year="2017 b">Cheek 2017b</bibRefCitation>
) for the IUCN Red List. The taxon is known only from the Mana River valley system in Cameroon. The extent of occurrence and the area of occupancy are both estimated at 2 km2 each. The assessment of 
<bibRefCitation author="Cheek, M" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B14" refString="Cheek, M, 2017b. Ledermanniellaprasina. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2017: e.T110079107A110079109. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" title="Ledermanniellaprasina. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2017: e. T 110079107 A 110079109. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" year="2017 b">Cheek (2017b)</bibRefCitation>
is maintained since no major changes have taken place at the locality since that assessment. The species is here reassessed as Vulnerable. IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Vulnerable VUB1+2ab (iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
